The 'Sportklub Rapid Wien' (known in English as 'Rapid Vienna') is an Austrian
football club playing in the country's capital city of Vienna. Rapid is the most
popular club in Austria, and also the most successful in terms of league titles.
It has won 32 Austrian league titles, and a German championship in 1941 during
Nazi rule. Rapid twice reached the final of the European Cup Winners' Cup in
1985 and 1996, losing on both occasions.
